{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The speech-to-text output preserves speaker labels so that the summary can attribute statements to specific attendees.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"MOCK-MISS: in-process mocks can validate wiring but miss diarization/label quality failures from the real speech model. REAL-INFRA exists (external API), but the core risk is model-produced speaker labeling correctness. LLM-DEP/ML-DEP applies because attribution quality depends on real model output, which can vary by audio.","test_description":"Run the service on real multi-speaker meeting audio through the real speech-to-text API, then generate summary and assert attendee attributions map to the correct speaker labels in the produced transcript/summary.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.28,"Agentic":0.48,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The structured summary contains at least one action item for every attendee who was assigned a task during the meeting.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"MOCK-HIDE: a mocked summarizer would trivially pass and hide extraction/coverage failures. Correctness is about semantic task assignment recall by the real LLM, not just schema validity. Outcomes can vary with model behavior/prompt sensitivity.","test_description":"Use real transcript inputs with known per-attendee task assignments, call the real LLM summarization step, and assert each assigned attendee appears with at least one action item in structured output.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Key decisions mentioned in the transcript appear in the \"decisions\" section of the summary, not buried in the narrative.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Failure boundary is semantic extraction + correct section placement by the LLM. Integration tests can check routing/format, but mocked or deterministic stubs miss real model misclassification and section drift.","test_description":"Feed transcripts containing explicit decision statements to the real summarization model and assert those decisions are present in the structured `decisions` field, with none only present in freeform narrative.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.72,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When the audio file is longer than 60 minutes, the service splits it into segments and processes them sequentially, merging the results into a single coherent summary.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: unit tests on splitter/merger alone can miss handoff bugs across orchestrator -> segment processor -> merger. REAL-INFRA is not strictly required to catch core failures (segment boundaries, ordering, merge state). Agentic quality is secondary to local sequencing/merge correctness for this behavior.","test_description":"With local/in-memory fakes for STT/LLM returning deterministic per-segment outputs, run a >60-minute input through orchestration and assert segment count, strict sequential processing order, and merged final structure includes all segment contributions without loss/duplication.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.16,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full pipeline — upload audio, transcribe, summarize, deliver structured output — completes without manual intervention for a real meeting recording.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"MULTI-STEP: this is explicitly end-to-end across multiple real agentic stages (speech model then LLM summarization) plus delivery. Mocking any major dependency can hide real cross-step failures (timeouts, format drift, retry edges, final delivery contract).","test_description":"Execute a production-like end-to-end run on a real meeting recording: upload, real STT call, real LLM summarization, and real output delivery endpoint/storage; assert successful completion, valid structured schema, and no manual recovery steps.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.18,"Agentic":0.22,"Workflow":0.55}}]}
